The Inter-Ministerial Committee dealing with Coronavirus will give an update on all matters pertaining to Coronavirus in South Africa. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - An Inter-Ministerial Committee dealing with coronavirus in South Africa will give an update on all matters pertaining to the outbreak. Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said South Africans shouldn't fear the coronavirus, but rather understand how to defeat it. READ: COVID-19: Egypt reports first confirmed virus death in Africa On Monday, Grayston Preparatory School closed its doors due to COVID-19 fears. And Africa recorded its first death after a German man died in an Egyptian hospital.